data.body:
add [pgvector types](https://github.com/pgvector/pgvector?tab=readme-ov-file#reference) to https://github.com/golemcloud/golem/blob/main/wit/deps/golem-rdbms/postgres.wit

* [vector](https://github.com/pgvector/pgvector?tab=readme-ov-file#vector-type)
* [halfvec](https://github.com/pgvector/pgvector?tab=readme-ov-file#halfvec-type)
* [sparsevec](https://github.com/pgvector/pgvector?tab=readme-ov-file#sparsevec-type)
* [bit](https://github.com/pgvector/pgvector?tab=readme-ov-file#bit-type) - this is already supported

wit changes:
```wit
  record sparse-vec {
    dim: s32,
    indices: list<s32>,
    values: list<f32>
  }

  variant db-column-type {
    // ...
    vector,
    halfvec,
    sparsevec
  } 

  variant db-value {
    // ...
    vector(list<f32>),
    halfvec(list<f32>), 
    sparsevec(sparse-vec)
  }
```
NOTE: as [wit](https://component-model.bytecodealliance.org/design/wit.html#primitive-types) do not have support for `f16`, `f32` is used in `db-value::halfvec`  wit type

